snippet: The streets were calm in the capital, Conakry, and elsewhere after deadly clashes last week between security forces and supporters of rival parties.
abstract: Guineans vote peacefully in country's second free election since it achieved independence from France almost 60 years ago; Pres Alpha Conde is expected to win, but results could lead to runoff between Conde and his chief rival Cellou Dalein Diallo.
lead_paragraph: The streets were calm in the capital, Conakry, and elsewhere after deadly clashes last week between security forces and supporters of rival parties.

headline.main: Calm in Guinea on Election Day
